  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with potentially severe legal consequences. Generally, if someone is caught laundering money, they may face:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal or state prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Significant potential prison time\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Potential Penalties\n- Prison sentences (often 5-20 years)\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Mandatory restitution\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\nThe exact consequences depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Specific methods used\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction of prosecution\n\nSpecific details can vary by jurisdiction, so consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate information for a particular situation.",
